Package: kwebdavfs-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: dkms, build-essential, linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-arm64
Description: kwebdavfs - WebDAV kernel filesystem (DKMS)
 A native kernel filesystem module that mounts WebDAV/Nextcloud shares
 directly via the Linux VFS layer, with no userspace helper required.
 .
 Features: directory listing cache with configurable TTL, read/write
 file access, mkdir, rename (MOVE), delete, and percent-encoded filenames.
 .
 This package uses DKMS to automatically build and install the module
 for every installed kernel version.
